### Secured Endpoints — request samples
### Set these variables, then run the requests below.

@baseUrl = https://<your-app-name>.azurewebsites.net
@contentType = application/json

# API key for the "apikey" agent (function key). Get it with:
#   az functionapp keys list -g rg-<env> -n <app-name> --query functionKeys.default -o tsv
@functionKey = <function-key>

# Bearer token for the "entra" agent. Get it with:
#   az account get-access-token --resource <your-audience> --query accessToken -o tsv
@bearerToken = <entra-access-token>

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API KEY AGENT  (builtin_endpoints.auth: function)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Chat WITHOUT key -> 401 Unauthorized
POST {{baseUrl}}/agents/apikey/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "prompt": "Say hello in one sentence"
}

### Chat WITH key (header) -> 200 OK
POST {{baseUrl}}/agents/apikey/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
x-functions-key: {{functionKey}}

{
  "prompt": "Say hello in one sentence"
}

### Chat WITH key (query string) -> 200 OK
POST {{baseUrl}}/agents/apikey/chat?code={{functionKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "prompt": "Say hello in one sentence"
}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ENTRA AGENT  (builtin_endpoints.auth.mode: entra)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Chat WITHOUT token -> 401 Unauthorized
POST {{baseUrl}}/agents/entra/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "prompt": "Say hello in one sentence"
}

### Chat WITH bearer token -> 200 OK
POST {{baseUrl}}/agents/entra/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{bearerToken}}

{
  "prompt": "Say hello in one sentence"
}
